Hungary May Need More Budget Reserves for GDP Slowdown, MTI Says

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-08-31T07:51:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/hungary-may-need-more-budget-reserves-for-gdp-slowdown-mti-says.html
Hungary  may need more budget
reserves than the 250 billion forint ($1.3 billion) allocated
this year against a slowdown in economic growth,  MTI  said,
citing an interview with  Mihaly Varga , chief of staff for the
prime minister, on the commercial TV station TV2.  The government may tighten taxes to close budget gaps and
raise the excise tax on cigarettes, MTI said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  